parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of airbags can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities. It can also lead to financial losses and emotional distress.

causing surprise and alarm to the driver and passengers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition coil failure can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and potentially lead to accidents.
Cooling system failure can cause engine overheating, engine damage, and potentially lead to accidents.
Catalytic converter failure can cause engine performance issues, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to accidents.
Electrical system failure can cause engine stalling, loss of vehicle control, and potentially lead to accidents.
Interior odors and fumes can cause health issues, discomfort, and distraction while driving.
Alternator failure can cause engine stalling, loss of vehicle control, and potentially lead to accidents.
The failure of the heated seat can cause burns to the driver or passenger, and in some cases, can lead to a fire, which can result in serious injury or even death.

symptoms: especially when cold; the vehicle loses power or acceleration; the transmission fails to engage into gear; the vehicle experiences hard shifting between gears.
